  "bib_entries": {
    "38061573": {
      "title": "Life with 482 genes",
      "abstract": "A. Goffeau discusses the implications of the sequencing of the second complete genome—that of the small parasite Mycoplasma genitalium —by C. Fraser et al. , reported in this issue of Science . This technically impressive achievement now allows identification of minimal sets of genes necessary for various biological functions and comparisons to other complete genome sequences."
